<h2>Resources in This Category</h2>
<ul>

    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.grandmagazine.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Grand Magazine: Community</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.grandmagazine.com/</strong></font> <br /> A national, print magazine for grandparents. Community includes chat, photo gallery and message boards.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.grandboomers.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Grandboomers</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.grandboomers.com/</strong></font> <br /> A site for babyboomers who are now grandparents, helping you in your new role in the family.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.grandloving.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Grandloving.com</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.grandloving.com/</strong></font> <br /> Website and book, devoted to keeping families close. Features an list of books for grandparents and grandchildren to share, as well as long-distance and do-together crafts for all ages.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.lapl.org/about/volunteer.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Grandparents and Books</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.lapl.org/about/volunteer.html</strong></font> <br /> Like books and kids? Be a library grandparent. Los Angeles Public Library describes their program and includes an application form.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="https://aga.grandparents.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Grandparents.com</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>https://aga.grandparents.com/</strong></font> <br /> Articles about health, finances, leisure activities, food, and grandkids, and information about membership in the American Grandparents Association.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.sptimes.com/News/012501/Floridian/How_grandparents_can_.shtml" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Keeping Grandkids Safe</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.sptimes.com/News/012501/Floridian/How_grandparents_can_.shtml</strong></font> <br /> A look at the all-important issue of safe sleep for infants, and how the guidelines have changed since today&#039;s baby boomers were &quot;just parents.&quot;</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.nafgpd.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>National Association of Foster Grandparent Program Directors</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.nafgpd.org/</strong></font> <br /> Professional membership organization advocating for foster grandparent programs. Offers history, membership and mission.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://fpb.case.edu/Grandmother/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Grandmother Study: Intergenerational Caregiving to Youth</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://fpb.case.edu/Grandmother/</strong></font> <br /> Examines the health status of grandmothers and the impact of grandmothers on their families. Offers description of study and timeline.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.legacyproject.org/grandparents.html" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Legacy Project</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.legacyproject.org/grandparents.html</strong></font> <br /> Offers books, research, and workshops on grandparenting, intergenerational relationships, literacy education, and science education. Includes grandparenting tips and book excerpts.</p>
    </li>	
</ul>

